  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are staging a risk-on rally driven by optimism around potential US-Iran peace talks, with stocks hitting new highs while the dollar weakens to six-week lows. Bitcoin is testing critical resistance at $75-76K amid institutional inflows but faces profit-taking pressure, while oil prices are declining on diplomatic hopes despite Middle East supply disruption concerns.",
    "regimeImpact": "The peace deal optimism is extending the oversold relief rally but remains fragile given the preliminary nature of talks and approaching Apr 2 tariff deadline.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR ladder strikes around $75K level as BTC faces resistance and profit-taking pressure with potential for pullback to $62.3K structural support",
      "Consider reducing short book exposure on risk-on momentum but maintain hedges given fragile nature of peace talks and binary catalysts ahead",
      "Hold Maturity sector overweight as lower yields from peace optimism favor defensive positioning while monitoring 10Y around 4.50% stress level"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "BTC stalling at $75-76K resistance with profit-taking despite institutional flows suggests consolidation phase ahead",
      "Dollar at six-week lows and declining oil prices indicate risk-on sentiment but dependent on fragile diplomatic progress",
      "Tech stocks driving indices to new highs while VIX remains elevated suggests cautious optimism rather than conviction rally",
      "Ethereum MACD golden cross and 74% historical gains pattern could signal crypto rotation if BTC consolidates"
    ]
